io.jsonwebtoken

Interface JwtHandler<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of object to return to the parser caller after handling the parsed JWT.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    JwtHandlerAdapter

    public interface JwtHandler<T>
    A JwtHandler is invoked by a JwtParser after parsing a JWT to indicate the exact type of JWT or JWS parsed.
    Since:
    0.2

    • Method Detail

      • onPlaintextJwt

        T onPlaintextJwt(Jwt<Header,String> jwt)
        This method is invoked when a JwtParser determines that the parsed JWT is a plaintext JWT. A plaintext JWT has a String (non-JSON) body payload and it is not cryptographically signed.
        Parameters:
        jwt - the parsed plaintext JWT
        Returns:
        any object to be used after inspecting the JWT, or null if no return value is necessary.

      • onClaimsJwt

        T onClaimsJwt(Jwt<Header,Claims> jwt)
        This method is invoked when a JwtParser determines that the parsed JWT is a Claims JWT. A Claims JWT has a Claims body and it is not cryptographically signed.
        Parameters:
        jwt - the parsed claims JWT
        Returns:
        any object to be used after inspecting the JWT, or null if no return value is necessary.

      • onPlaintextJws

        T onPlaintextJws(Jws<String> jws)
        This method is invoked when a JwtParser determines that the parsed JWT is a plaintext JWS. A plaintext JWS is a JWT with a String (non-JSON) body (payload) that has been cryptographically signed.

        This method will only be invoked if the cryptographic signature can be successfully verified.

        Parameters:
        jws - the parsed plaintext JWS
        Returns:
        any object to be used after inspecting the JWS, or null if no return value is necessary.

      • onClaimsJws

        T onClaimsJws(Jws<Claims> jws)
        This method is invoked when a JwtParser determines that the parsed JWT is a valid Claims JWS. A Claims JWS is a JWT with a Claims body that has been cryptographically signed.

        This method will only be invoked if the cryptographic signature can be successfully verified.

        Parameters:
        jws - the parsed claims JWS
        Returns:
        any object to be used after inspecting the JWS, or null if no return value is necessary.
